The guide’s deepest design rule

After scanning all rows, the source consistently behaves like this:

It always chooses the easiest spatial metaphor

not the most academically precise one.

Examples:
	•	hash logic becomes a lookup board
	•	linked list logic becomes a rewiring diagram
	•	SQL becomes row movement
	•	DP becomes arrows into cells
	•	sliding window becomes brackets on a strip
	•	binary lifting becomes jump blocks
	•	carry math becomes column arithmetic

So the guide is not trying to classify algorithms perfectly.

It is trying to answer:

“What picture makes the idea obvious fastest?”

That is the real anatomy of the entire project.

