9) How to draw helper structures

Helper structures are often the real optimized engine.

9.1 Hash map / set

Draw:
	•	2-column table or bucket board
	•	key → value
	•	or just key buckets if set

Example:
7 -> 1
2 -> 0

9.2 Queue

Draw:
	•	horizontal or vertical lane
	•	front/back clearly labeled

9.3 Stack

Draw:
	•	vertical pile
	•	top labeled

9.4 Heap

Draw:
	•	either as a heap tree
	•	or as a priority funnel with top element highlighted

9.5 DP table

Draw:
	•	row or grid
	•	arrows showing dependencies
	•	current cell highlighted

9.6 Prefix/suffix arrays

Draw:
	•	original strip
	•	helper strip below/above

9.7 Visited/Distance

Draw:
	•	directly on nodes/cells when possible
