10) How to draw updates

Variables are not enough.
You must show how they change.

Use these update styles:

A. Motion arrow

For pointers moving:
	•	R++
	•	L--
	•	move to next node

B. Value replacement

Show old → new

Example:
sum: 10 -> 15

C. Increment/decrement marker

Example:
count[a] += 1

D. Rewire arrow

For linked lists/trees

E. Color/state change

For visited/settled/active

F. Layer transition

For BFS / process simulation

G. State fill

For DP cells

The rule is:

If the viewer cannot see what changed, the variables are not doing useful visual work.

