3. Border system

Border style	Meaning
Thin solid	Neutral input / inactive structure
Thick solid	Active this frame
Dashed	Helper / derived / support structure
Double line	Final / settled / returned
Dotted	Candidate / hypothetical / not yet committed
Slashed / X	Invalid / removed / rejected

Examples:
	•	current dp[i][j] cell = thick solid
	•	hash map = dashed
	•	final answer = double line
	•	popped stack item = slashed

⸻

4. Fill / emphasis system

Fill style	Meaning
No fill	Neutral / background input
Light fill	Relevant but unchanged this frame
Dark fill / heavy highlight	Changed this frame / active now
Faded / ghosted	Past state / low-priority context
Dotted pattern	Visited / cached / memoized
Diagonal stripes	Blocked / forbidden / obstacle
Cross-hatch	Danger / conflict / overlap hotspot

