9) The four memory labels every diagram should consider

A strong memory diagram should label memory as one or more of:

Input

Already given

Aux

Algorithm’s extra memory

Temp

Temporary/transient memory

Output

Returned/stored result

Example:
	•	Input = O(n)
	•	Aux = O(n)
	•	Temp = O(1)
	•	Output = O(k)

This is much better than only saying “Space = O(n)”.

